<h2>1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
<p>Cookies are small text files that are stored on your device when you visit a website. They help the website remember your preferences and improve your experience.</p>

<h2>2. How We Use Cookies</h2>
<p>Desco Lead CRM uses only <strong>essential cookies</strong> that are strictly necessary for the platform to function. We do <strong>not</strong> use advertising, tracking, or analytics cookies.</p>

<h3>2.1 Essential Cookies</h3>
<div class="info-card">
  <h4><i class="fas fa-lock"></i> Session Cookie</h4>
  <p><strong>Name:</strong> connect.sid</p>
  <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Maintains your authenticated session after login. Without this cookie, you would need to log in on every page.</p>
  <p><strong>Duration:</strong> Expires when you log out or after 7 days of inactivity.</p>
  <p><strong>Type:</strong> Strictly necessary — cannot be disabled.</p>
</div>

<h2>3. Cookies We Do NOT Use</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Advertising cookies</strong> — We do not display ads or track users for advertising</li>
  <li><strong>Analytics cookies</strong> — We do not use Google Analytics or similar tracking</li>
  <li><strong>Third-party cookies</strong> — We do not embed third-party tracking scripts</li>
  <li><strong>Social media cookies</strong> — We do not embed social media tracking pixels</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Managing Cookies</h2>
<p>Since we only use essential cookies required for authentication, disabling them will prevent you from logging into the CRM dashboard. You can manage cookies through your browser settings:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Chrome:</strong> Settings → Privacy and Security → Cookies</li>
  <li><strong>Firefox:</strong> Settings → Privacy & Security → Cookies</li>
  <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences → Privacy → Cookies</li>
  <li><strong>Edge:</strong> Settings → Cookies and Site Permissions</li>
</ul>

